#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:827
msgid "Secure Cookies"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:833
msgid "Enable Secure Cookies"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:834
msgid "Enforcing all cookies are set as secure adds a layer of protection against cross-site scripting attacks and is an easy measure to protect your website."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:836
msgid "These settings are added to your wp-config.php file."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:863
msgid "Security Headers"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:864
msgid "Configuring your website with the right security headers can help your website from a lot of problems. It can be difficult to get the settings right, so be sure to test your website properly."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:868
msgid "LiteSpeed detected:"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:868
msgid "The PHP header interface may not work on LiteSpeed servers. If security headers do not appear in your response, add them directly to your .htaccess file (see the test descriptions for each header for examples)."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:878
msgid "Hide PHP Version"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:879
msgid "Removes the \"X-Powered-By\" header. No need to tell what software version you are running."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:899
msgid "X-Content-Type-Options"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:900
msgid "Setting this will force a browser to only load external resources (.css, .js and so on) if the content-type matches what is expected. This prevents malicious hidden code in unexpected files."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:920 modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:950 modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:976 modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1002
#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1033
msgid "Default: "
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:927
msgid "X-Frame-Options"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:928 sn-tests-description.php:104
msgid ""
"The X-Frame-Options response header indicates if a page is allowed to render a page in an iframe, frame or object. Avoid clickjacking attacks simply by not allowing your content to be embedded on other websites."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:929
msgid "Note: Content-Security-Policy with the frame-ancestors directive is the modern alternative, but X-Frame-Options is still widely supported and valid."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:955
msgid "Strict-Transport-Security"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:956
msgid "When enabled, HSTS instructs browsers to only connect to your website using HTTPS, preventing SSL stripping attacks and ensuring all data transmission is encrypted."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:981
msgid "Referrer-Policy"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1001
msgid ""
"Referrer-Policy is a way to control when the \"referrer\" header information is allowed. This means which websites can see where visitors are referred from. The recommended setting \"same-origin\" allows you to "
"still track data internally on your website."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1009
msgid "Permissions-Policy"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1010
msgid "This is a way to instruct a browser which features it can use on a website. With this you can explicitly prevent access to the camera, microphone, geolocation and many other features."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1032
msgid "For a full and updated list check out the link: "
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1032
msgid "Mozilla.org - Permissions Policy"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1034
msgid "Note: This was previously named Feature Policy. Both the name and the syntax have been changed since then."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1040
msgid "Content-Security-Policy"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1041
msgid "Warning: If you embed scripts from external websites, Google Analytics or other sources this could break your website functionality. Read and test before implementing."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1042 modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1063 sn-tests-description.php:73
msgid "Since each website is different, we can only give a general suggestion and strongly advise to remove the fix again if something on your website stops working."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1043
msgid "Note: Content-Security-Policy is the modern replacement for the deprecated X-XSS-Protection header and provides more comprehensive protection against XSS attacks."
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1065
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1066
msgid "All is allowed, but only in code coming from this website:"
msgstr ""

#: modules/auto-fixer/class-wf-sn-fixes.php:1067
